The paper proposes a new class of Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) for computing position-aware node embeddings, which can be applied to multiple prediction tasks including link prediction and community detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the primary focus of the paper. The paper also involves the use of non-linear distance-weighted aggregation scheme, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper incorporates node feature information, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper applies P-GNNs to image data, which is related to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
